text.section:
The secretary shall adopt standards, by administrative regulation pursuant to KRS Chapter 13A, for the operation of boarding homes. The administrative regulations shall include minimum requirements in the following areas:
Minimum room sizes for rooms occupied for sleeping purposes. Rooms occupied by one (1) boarding home resident shall contain at least sixty (60) square feet of floor space. Rooms occupied by more than one (1) occupant shall contain at least forty (40) square feet of floor space for each occupant;
Bedding, linens, and laundry services provided to residents;
Sanitary and plumbing fixtures, water supply, sewage disposal, and sanitation of the premises;
Heating, lighting, and fire prevention, including the installation and maintenance of smoke detectors;
Maintenance of the building;
Food handling, preparation, and storage, and kitchen sanitation;
Nutritional standards sufficient to meet the boarder's need;
Complaint procedures whereby residents may lodge complaints with the cabinet concerning the operation of the boarding home; and
Initial and periodic screening procedures to ensure that individuals meet the definition of "boarder" under KRS 216B.300(3).
